=====Usage notes=====
In Middle and Modern Korean, the [[allomorph]] taken by the topic marker after a vowel may be {{ko-inline|는|tr=-neun}} instead of {{ko-inline|ㄴ|tr=-n}}, especially in formal speech. This is the result of [[reduplication]] of the topic marker at some point and may not have been present in Old Korean, although the phonologically opaque nature of the orthography makes it difficult to tell.

